717320f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 12th Street
717320f-a.text:
Broadway, east side, from 14th to lNth Streets. The Demarest
Building on the S.e. corner of 14th Street, built by the Domestic
Sewing Machine Company in 1872, was at that time the highest build
1ng in New York, and was so advertised. It will be replaced by a
twenty-three story building between 1925 and 1930. The Roosevelt
Building, which adjoins it, wull stand in 1936.
About 1921.
Edwin Levick.
